# Quarterly persona & pricing recalibration (light, monthly check-in)

## Intent

Pricing & ICP still match reality: paid-cohort signal reviewed, ICP one-liner adjusted, one price experiment queued or rejected, free-to-paid funnel decision recorded.

## Scope

Pricing & ICP still match reality: paid-cohort signal reviewed, ICP one-liner adjusted, one price experiment queued or rejected, free-to-paid funnel decision recorded.

## Stages

### 1. Re-read paid-cohort signal

Look at who is actually paying, not who you imagined.

Tasks:
- Pull the latest paid-cohort breakdown by use-case
- Note the dominant 2-3 use-cases
- Flag any drift from the imagined ICP

Outputs:
- Paid-cohort breakdown
- Top use-cases
- ICP drift notes

Decision gate: Advance only with a written drift verdict.

### 2. Adjust ICP one-liner

Re-write the ICP one-liner to match reality.

Tasks:
- Re-write the ICP one-liner
- Run it past 2 paying customers
- Roll into landing + onboarding copy

Outputs:
- New ICP one-liner
- Customer reactions
- Rollout note

Decision gate: Advance only when 2 customers confirm the new one-liner fits.

### 3. Queue or reject one price experiment

One disciplined pricing move per cycle.

Tasks:
- List pricing levers (anchor, tier, packaging, discount)
- Pick one experiment OR explicitly defer
- Pre-register the metric + sample size

Outputs:
- Experiment spec OR rejection note
- Pre-registered metric
- Schedule slot

Decision gate: Advance only when one decision is committed (queue or reject).

### 4. Free-to-paid funnel call

Audit the conversion path quarterly.

Tasks:
- Pull free-to-paid conversion rate by cohort
- Inspect onboarding emails and prompts
- Decide: change copy / change product / change pricing

Outputs:
- Conversion-rate snapshot
- Onboarding audit
- Decision note

Decision gate: Advance only when there is a single named change to ship.

### 5. Document the recalibration

Lock the quarters position in writing.

Tasks:
- Write the quarterly recalibration entry
- Update the pricing card if changed
- Set the next quarterly checkpoint

Outputs:
- Recalibration doc
- Pricing card update (if any)
- Next checkpoint reminder

Decision gate: Cycle closes when the recalibration doc is committed.

## Common pitfalls

- Skipping the decision-gate write-up to keep moving - closes the loop with vibes, not evidence.
- Treating each stages outputs as optional - every output is a gate input for the next stage.
- Letting one bad week stretch a fixed-cadence ritual into a quarterly one.

## Quality checklist

- Every stage has at least one referenced methodology that resolves under `knowledge/`.
- Every output is a real artefact, not a feeling.
- The final decision is a written commitment, not we will see.
